            "title": "Cathie Wood's ARK Innovation ETF (ARKK) surged 50% in last 3 months, outperforming S&P 500, despite being 50% lower than Feb 2021 peak.",
            "id": "ab96b185-f165-4646-a95e-356768900199",
            "description": "In the peak of the pandemic in 2020, Cathie Wood's Ark Innovation ETF (NYSE: ARKK) experienced a significant surge, increasing almost 400% from its low point in March 2020. However, this momentum came to a halt in February 2021 with ARKK plummeting close to 80% due to rising inflation and interest rates. The fund struggled with declining valuations and decreasing interest in unprofitable growth stocks. Presently, ARKK is still down by 50% compared to its peak in February 2021, but there are signs of a resurgence. Over the last three months, ARKK has surged by an impressive 50%, representing its most robust rally since 2021. This is nearly double the performance of the S&P 500, tracked by the Vanguard S&P 500 ETF (NYSE: VOO), during the same period. The complete article is accessible at Benzinga.com.",
